-- Nippon, Tata Steel May Be in Talks on India Blast Furnace, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2010-09-29T17:07:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/steelmakers-nippon-tata-in-talks-on-venture-to-produce-in-indian-market.html
Nippon Steel Corp. and Tata Steel
Ltd. may be in negotiations to build a blast furnace in India
through a joint venture as early as 2013, Nikkei English News
reported, without saying how it obtained the information.  Nippon Steel wants to increase local production in India to
weather a strong yen, and to tap overseas demand, Nikkei
reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  